17/02/2004
MOSCOW, Russia -- Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy arrived in Russia late Monday (16 February) to discuss joint sea transport projects and boosting Russian gas and oil transit through Bulgarian territory. Also on the agenda were anti-terrorism efforts, the crisis in the Trans-Dniester region, participation of OSCE observers in Russia's 14 March presidential elections and events marking 125 years of diplomatic ties. Passy is discussing Russian relations with the OSCE in his capacity as the organisation's new chairman-in-office. (bTV, BTA - 17/02/04; BTA, BNT - 16/02/04)
